Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%pack}. Pop into a #medium bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork (or a #potato masher{}).

Trim the @scallion{1}(trimmed) then slice thinly. Add the scallion, @grated cheese{50%g}, @chipotle paste{1%sachet} and @tomato paste{1%sachet} to the beans. Season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Mix well.

Lay half the @tortilla{4%units} (double for 4p) out on a #board. Spread a little of the bean mix over half of each, leaving a small border around the edge. Fold the tortillas in half to make half-moon shapes.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{to taste} in a #large pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, carefully lay the quesadillas in the pan. Fry until golden, ~{2%minutes} each side. Turn carefully. Lightly press down on them with a #spatula{} to ensure they stick together and brown nicely.

> You might have to do this in batches. Add more oil to the pan as needed and cover cooked quesadillas with foil to keep warm.

== Salad ==

While the quesadillas are frying, trim half the @cucumber{1/2%unit}(trimmed, quartered lengthways then chopped widthways) (double for 4p). Halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet} with 1 tbsp oil (double for 4p). Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @salad leaves{40%g}, tomatoes and cucumber and toss gently.

Serve the quesadillas alongside plenty of salad.